National Assembly: Discussion on the President responses on the allegations related to the misuse of public funds, Virtual Meeting Platform, 16th February 2022, 18:30-21:00 CAPE TOWN - The Standing Committee on Public Accounts will discuss President Cyril Ramaphosa's response to the allegations related to the misuse of public funds by the ANC. Ramaphosa sent a letter to SCOPA denying any first-hand knowledge of the abuse of state funding for ANC campaigns. READ: Mervyn Dirks Complaint | Scopa receives Ramaphosa's response The president was responding to a request from SCOPA for his comment on a leaked recording in which he alluded to the misuse of public funds. Suspended ANC member Mervyn Dirks asked SCOPA to investigate this.